# Microsoft Foundry IQ integration (client-side runtime defaults)
# Do NOT store real keys in source control. .env files are gitignored.
#
# Three operating modes are supported, switchable in the UI:
#  - relay  : calls /api/chat on this site (SWA Managed Function w/ MI). No token needed.
#  - bearer : calls the Foundry data plane directly with an Entra bearer token.
#  - api-key: same, but with an api-key header (requires disableLocalAuth=false).
#
# Default below uses the dev-time Vite proxy at /foundry so you can validate
# the bearer flow locally without standing up the SWA. Switch the UI dropdown
# to "Hosted relay" once deployed.
VITE_FOUNDRY_IQ_ENDPOINT_URL=/foundry
VITE_FOUNDRY_IQ_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-41-mini
VITE_FOUNDRY_IQ_API_VERSION=2025-01-01-preview
VITE_FOUNDRY_IQ_AUTH_MODE=bearer

# Optional: override the dev proxy target without editing vite.config.ts
# VITE_FOUNDRY_PROXY_TARGET=https://<your-account>.cognitiveservices.azure.com
